# Image Placeholder Instructions

## Quick Setup Guide for Images

This folder should contain your portfolio images. Follow these steps:

### Option 1: Download Manually (Recommended)

1. Visit **Unsplash.com** and search for:
   - "education classroom" → Save as `education.jpg`
   - "Indigenous community" → Save as `land-acknowledgement.jpg`
   - "diverse learning group" → Save as `indigenous-learning.jpg`
   - "community hands together" → Save as `allyship.jpg`
   - "teaching environment" → Save as `profile-bg.jpg`
   - "growth journey" → Save as `coming-soon.jpg`

2. Save each image with the exact filename shown in the table below

3. Place all images in this `images/` folder

### Required Image Files

| Filename | Minimum Size | Purpose |
|----------|--------------|---------|
| profile-bg.jpg | 350×280px | Header background |
| education.jpg | 600×500px | About Me section |
| land-acknowledgement.jpg | 600×400px | Module 1 - Takeaway 1 |
| indigenous-learning.jpg | 600×400px | Module 1 - Takeaway 2 |
| allyship.jpg | 600×400px | Module 1 - Takeaway 3 |
| coming-soon.jpg | 400×350px | Other Modules placeholder |

### Option 2: Using a Script

If you have `curl` or `wget` installed, run this command from the `images/` folder:

```bash
# Example: Download education image from Unsplash
curl -o education.jpg "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1427504494785-cdec0f72b686?w=600&q=80"
```

---

**Once images are added, delete this file and your portfolio will display correctly!**
